WEBVTT

00:00.520 --> 00:02.960
From what you told me, it sounds like these factors

00:02.960 --> 00:05.760
are your biggest sleep disruptors.

00:05.760 --> 00:08.620
You'd be surprised how common these issues are,

00:08.620 --> 00:12.540
especially waking up sore, tossing and turning,

00:12.540 --> 00:15.640
or never quite feeling rested.

00:15.640 --> 00:20.080
Research finds that 70% of us struggle to fall asleep.

00:20.080 --> 00:23.200
Nearly everyone who struggles to fall asleep wakes up

00:23.200 --> 00:25.480
at least once during the night.

00:25.480 --> 00:28.400
That means we can often wake up feeling tired,

00:28.400 --> 00:30.640
groggy and grumpy.

00:30.640 --> 00:31.940
If you leave your email,

00:31.940 --> 00:35.040
I can prepare a personalized sleep report for you.

00:36.160 --> 00:39.920
It will be in your inbox in less than five minutes.

